nocracy?\nNot only is organized labor a victim\nof selfish despoilers, but the small\ncompetitor has been brought face to\nface, with the inevitable, the survival\nof the fittest in the business and com\nmercial world, which in turn inevit\nably concentrates wealth in fewer\nhands.\nIt is the writers opinion that in\nstead of the foundation of Democracy,\nthe foundation of an Empire is being\nlaid in th? United States. Tile owners\nof American wealth, many of then\n[foreigners, have been moulded grad\nrally into a ruling class.\nThe empty shops and the general\n[attitude of the capitalistic press is a\nglaring example of the natural out\ngrowth of an invisible power which\nhas been developed. Coming events\ncast their shadows before, and we\nlaboring men have long since been\naware of the approaching danger.\nIn view of the fact that th\u00b0 press\ndtpends for the most part upon the\nadvertisements received from the*\nmerchants, and the merchant in turn\ndepends upon the purchasing power\nof those who labor, it is a matter that\nbaffles the- mind of the w*ber vhy\nboth part.es so frequently igiore the\nworkers.\nIt was the immortal- Lincoln who\nsaid: \u201cThey err in vision they\nstumble in judgement. Labor is prior\nMEN\u2019S SHIRTS\n49\nMen\u2019s New Spring Dress Shirts of\nMadras and Percale, 14 to 17^.\nBOYS\u2019 PANTS 83C\nBoys\u2019 New Spring Knee Pants, nov\nelty mixture or corduroy.\nSpecial Sale at 88c.\nMEN\u2019S WORK 4Q\nPANTS\n1.417\nGood Weight Dark Striped Mixture,\nsizes 29\nto 42 waist.\nMEN\u2019S 29c HOSE,\nWORK OR DRESS\nLADIES\u2019 LISLE\n0c\nFEFSODENT\nto and independent of capitil. Cap\nital is only the fruit of labor,\nand could never have existed if labor\nhad not first existed. Labor is the\nsuperior of capital, and deserves\nmuch higher consideration.\u201d\nThe present business depression,\nthe empty shops and the purchase\npower of the working people reduced\nto almost nothing, due to America\u2019s\nwealth being controled by a few men,\nis a condition that should bring the\nmerchants and the press to realize\nthe truthfulness of the words of\nLincoln.\nthe\nQf\nthe\nfood for thought, and wn?n\nbrings us down to this\nAre we living in a dem-\n15c\n4 0-\nHOSE\nLadies\u2019 Fine Mercerized Lisle Hose,\nformerly priced 75c, now 49c.\nBAYERS\u2019 ASPIRIN\nTABLETS\nTwo Dozen Bayer\u2019s Aspirin\nin screw cap bottle, 25c.\n25c\nTablets\n.A UN DRY SOAP,\n0 BARS\n.0 Bars Climax of Hammer\n'oap, 33c.\n33c\nLaundry\nSNERGINE DRY\nJLEANSER\n23c\n35c\nTOOTH PASTE\n30c LUXOR FACE\nPOWDER, FOR\nDJERKISS ROUGE,\nFOR\nLAYMAN\u2019S SOAP\nSPECIAL\nTown Topics\nCarnival Company Coming\nThe Burns Carnival Company will\nopen a weeks engagement at the\nfair grounds beginning May 9.\n35c\n40c\nHome From Florida\nMrs. H. W. Wright, of Buena Vista\nstreet, returned home last week from\na month\u2019s visit to St. Augustin? and\nJacksonville, Florida.\nBack In Harness\nAfter a vacation of several months\nour associate editor has resumed his\nduties, and another interesting article\nfrom his versatile pen appears in this\nissue. Don\u2019t fail to read it, it\u2019s full\nof meat.\nCity Dumping Ground\nThe city has established a public\ndumping ground for rubbish only, in\nthe rear of the old municipal b\u2019/ht\nplant north of the North Fork of\nLicking river, and a man from the\nservice department will bo on duty\ndaily from seven in the mo-ning until\nfour in the afternoon. Entrance to\nthe ground is at the west end of\nEast Main street bridge.\nAmuwi.gr--\nTHE NEWARK LEADER\nassert that it\nthe best inter\na whole if all\nlife would lend\nThus it suffices\nwould be conducive\nests of the nation\npeople in all walks\nhand of good fellowship instead\nrepeated attempts to humiliate\u2019\nworkers.\nto\nto\nas\nof\nthe\nElk\u2019s Inspection at Columbus\nThe date for the inspection of\nColumbus Lodge of Elks, which was\npostponed on account of the illness of\nDistrict Deputy Harry Hale, has been\nset for March 30